wikipedia_page.main: Frederick St George Unwin (23 April 1911 – 4 October 1990) was an English cricketer. He played for Essex between 1932 and 1951 as a right-handed lower-order batsman, and captained the team in 1939.

response: On the cricket field, Unwin made seven first-class appearances with Essex throughout the 1930s. The Haileybury educated sportsman also played a bit of cricket for Suffolk in the Minor Counties His brother Frederick Unwin was a more successful cricketer, playing 53 first-class matches for Essex.
